modules.description: This module implements a rate limiter for controlling data transmission speeds in asynchronous file transfers. It works with byte rate limits specified in bytes per second and tracks the state of data sent over time. Concrete use cases include throttling network uploads or limiting disk I/O during file copying operations.

This module provides a rate limiter for controlling data transmission speeds during asynchronous file transfers, working with byte rate limits and tracking sent data over time. It includes a function to send the contents of a file to a file descriptor using `sendfile(2)`, optionally applying rate limiting and specifying transfer units. Concrete use cases include throttling network uploads and managing disk I/O during large file copies.
